caption: There pretzel mini dogs taste great.
Awesome. Great foot service and prices..

Great and fun place go work. And we are currently hiring!!!! Feel free to hop on indeed and type in auntie anne's westshore plaza. And just a tip feel bringing your resume and certs to the interview will score you point with the interviewer. And so will prior experience.😉

All though I love their pretzels this location needs to get it together. I came to the mall just to get a pretzel and the case at auntie Anne’s was completely empty. It was a slow day (Monday afternoon) and when I asked why there were no pretzels I was told they ran out. I have never seen this before where it was just an empty case. Usually I would assume they make some when it starts to get low. The boy in front continued making pretzel dogs with out asking what i wanted. After about 5 minutes he called into the back and a girl came out to take my order that was just sitting in the back. I found the whole situation very unprofessional.

Surprised with the amount of negative reviews, I was considering not consuming at this store. I gave it the benefit of the doubt.  The staff was very friendly and courteous. Very good service. I hope the store has improved since the last reviews. I got a peach lemonade frost and pretzel bites
Please just so close this place down they are very rude and delusional they own a cell not even working as we speak

Extremely rude and rushed. Like she has something better to do than wait on her only customer in an hour... Obviously the owners pay no attention to the continued bad reviews over the past 2 years. Vote with your feet and just keep walking!
Always look forward to coming here when I go to a mall.
So on top of them charging $9 for a small drink and cup of pretzel nuggets they want to charge $ for water too, really. I guess I don’t get it.

Treated my wife and I horribly. This was piled on top of already noticing that all three workers were angry and miserable. Westshore should be worried about this place. The experience at this place was so bad we left the entire mall.

Went there about 45 minutes ago to get the mini pretzel dogs and the pepperoni pretzels.. only to be told that they were in the process of closing, so they were shutting down.. so I asked what do you have? She told me whatever they had they gave away so they could clean up.. It was only 8:00 .. checked their hours online.. open till 9:30..REALLY.. Whoever is in charge of that stores needs to check up on their employees .
Terrible customer service! The cashier was on her phone, gave me a smart remark when I asked her a question and rolled her eyes at me! So very rude to all customers I saw her encounter!

This is indeed a very bad place to visit if you are at Westshore Plaza. The bad product quality is nothing compared with the extremely rude and unprofessional staff working here... what a shame for this place
Nice
Refused to make fresh product an hour before closing.

Always have an issue with this Auntie Ann's. It's either something is forgotten, burnt or rude customer service. This go around was something was forgotten that I was charged for. I tried calling the number but no one never answer.

Horrible service we wanted to buy a classic pretzel and they told us that it will be ready in 10 minutes so we came back after a whole hour 5:05 pm and they told us they were closed and we asked untill what time they were supposed to be open and they said 6:00pm so i dont understand the lack of empathy the company is losing money and its giving a bad experience for customers.
The employees are lazy and extremely slow.
Completely ridiculous! Over charging orders, not handing out complete orders,  disrespectful,  mocking us when we complained. Never again.  Deserving of zero stars and avoid this terrible location.

I would do zero stars if it could. This place over charged for a simple nugget meal. Argued with me about it and then said that they would give me $.88. Charging for individual items and then not giving them out. My sister paid $16 for pretzel nuggets and two drinks. This is the worst location I have ever been to and can’t understand why anyone would choose to get something from these unprofessional morons. Don’t go here.

The worst Auntie Anne's location Ive ever been to!  I work nearby, so Im at the mall frequently, and I would stop by here frequently too. Almost every time I walk away, because everything is burnt or way over cooked, or they dont have much out. I've never walked away from another Auntie Anne's before, yet this one ALWAYS sucks! I dont have time to wait around for a fresh pretzel to be cooked, they should always be fresh and not burnt!  Corporate needs to check in on this place, its horrible!

Terrible service. This is the only Auntie Anne's I've ever been to where you have to put in an order for a classic pretzel. I don't understand why you wouldnt have any ready for purchase. I waited 10 min and when I came back up for the pretzel I was told none were made because I didnt order it even though I asked before I sat there wasting my time. The employees act like they're on drugs and dont understand anything. I will never return or recommend this location to anyone!!

The are too busy trying to clean telling customers it will be a 35 min Waite to get the items there are three people and the are all too busy talking instead of working  the worst anti anne’s I have ever been too now I see why there reviews are only one star you need to watch the cameras so you see what they are doing before you go out of business I want to speak with the owner or the manager

The crew that served us 9.27.2017 was very unprofessional 3 people were on the clock nothing was ready. Pretzels were old we asked for fresh ones they told us to wait 8-15 mins we come back 15 minutes later and she tells us that we didn't  have a order for us... bad customer service no apologies was made this made me never want to come back... i wish i could give the service 0 stars
Don't have anything ready. Thats not profesional. I never come back
Best pretzels around!
You have to either get an Orange Julius and/or an Auntie Anne's pretzel to complete your mall experience.
